lightfield (1.0.8.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * New: "Wireframe" view mode.
  * Changed: File tab: When viewing models on the USB stick, the "Select" button now reads "Copy to library". Tapping it copies the selected model into the printer's model libary, then switches back to the model library view with the newly-copied model already selected.
  * Bug fix: The current selection is now cleared when switching between model library view and USB stick view. This should resolve intermittent difficulties with selecting models.

 -- LightField packager <lightfield-packager@volumetricbio.com>  Thu, 29 Aug 2019 17:24:27 -0700

lightfield (1.0.7.0) stable; urgency=medium

  * New: "Build platform offset" slider on Advanced tab. Defaults to 300 µm, range 0-1000 µm in steps of 25 µm.
  * New: "Project focus image" button on Advanced tab.
  * New: System tab will show a star icon if a USB stick containing a newer version of the LightField software has been inserted.
  * Changed: Scrollbar thumbs ought to be easier to hit now.
  * Changed: The "Projector floodlight" button on the Advanced tab is now called "Project blank image".
  * Changed: The "Print…" button on the Print tab now reads "Continue…".
  * Changed: The list of software updates has been made wider.
  * Changed: "Raise build platform" no longer locks out other functionality until "Lower build platform" is tapped.
  * Fixed: "Copy files to USB" should work now.
  * Fixed: The amount indicated by the "Dispense print solution" step should always be correct now.

